---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../../components/SiteNav.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Examples | Linkar" description="Explore the bundled Linkar example packs, from minimal shell templates to chaining, binding overrides, pack selection, and remote assets.">
  <div class="page-shell">
    <SiteNav />
    <main class="section-page">
      <section class="page-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Examples</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">Bundled packs you can read and run.</h1>
        <p class="lede page-lede">
          The example packs are meant to teach the product model in a sequence, not just provide
          random sample files.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section page-section-tight">
        <div class="card-grid two-up">
          <article class="feature-card">
            <h3>Basic</h3>
            <p>
              Minimal templates that show the runtime contract clearly: shell entrypoints,
              explicit defaults, local test entrypoints, and small Pixi-backed examples.
            </p>
            <pre><code>examples/packs/basic
  simple_echo
  simple_file_input
  simple_boolean_flag
  download_test_data
  fastq_stats
  pixi_echo
  pixi_pytest</code></pre>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <h3>Chaining</h3>
            <p>
              Shows how one template can consume another template’s outputs through pack-level
              binding defaults.
            </p>
            <pre><code>examples/packs/chaining
  linkar_pack.yaml
  templates/
    produce_message
    consume_message</code></pre>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <h3>Binding overrides</h3>
            <p>
              Demonstrates default binding behavior and explicit override binding so the same
              template can consume different sources predictably.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature-card">
            <h3>Pack management and remote</h3>
            <p>
              Covers duplicate template ids, active-pack selection, and Git-backed pack assets
              without turning Linkar into a registry-first product.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
